parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gaskets can cause coolant and oil to mix, leading to engine shutdown, overheating, and potential fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The vehicle catching fire can result in injuries, fatalities, and property damage.
symptoms: fire appeared to have started from underneath the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause a loss of braking ability, leading to extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.

the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard.
